benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC29 cover successful creation with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC08 covers malformed request body, missing required fields, invalid types.
Missing required header X-Killbill-CreatedBy: @TC09 covers missing header scenario.
No request body: @TC10 covers missing request body scenario.
Invalid bundleId format: @TC06 covers invalid format, @TC07 covers non-existent bundleId.
Bundle not found: @TC05, @TC07 scenarios cover no data or non-existent bundle cases.
Maximum/minimum values: @TC13, @TC14 scenarios test boundary values.
Partial input: @TC15 covers partial data submission.
Special characters/XSS: @TC23, @TC24 scenarios address special character handling.
Concurrency and network issues: @TC21, @TC22 scenarios address retries and concurrent requests.
Regression tests: @TC23, @TC24 ensure backward compatibility and previous bug fixes.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or missing authentication tokens.
Rate Limiting: No tests for handling multiple requests in rapid succession.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Pagination: No tests for handling large datasets or paginated responses.
Service Unavailability: Limited coverage (@TC17) for service downtime or dependency errors.
Injection attempts: Limited to @TC19, but no comprehensive tests for various injection vectors.
Stress testing with very large payloads (@TC16, @TC27) is partially covered but could be expanded.
Accessibility: Only @TC30 addresses documentation accessibility, not API accessibility features.
recommendations: Add tests for authorization headers and invalid tokens to ensure proper access control.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system handles high request volumes gracefully.
Include scenarios testing cache headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Develop pagination tests for large datasets to verify correct handling of paged responses.
Expand testing for service unavailability, including dependency failures and retries.
Create comprehensive injection and XSS tests across all input fields to ensure security.
Increase stress testing with larger payloads and concurrent requests to evaluate system robustness.
Add accessibility testing for API documentation and consider accessibility in API responses.
